say stanford anthology for youth home writing workshops anthology information spring convention contact us volunteering run by students at stanford university stanford anthology for youth is a non profit organization that offers local students in grades 6 8 an opportunity to express their literary creativity in an annual collection of student works which is published at the end of school year our goals are simple to promote writing reveal potential and inspire personal expression in a joint creative voice regardless of age gender ethnicity or economic status throughout the school year say teaches free in school creative writing workshops to spark students interest in writing if you are a parent teacher or student interested in participating in our program click here
